{
  "id": "019d2fb2-4a12-7e23-8577-4c83057c0da9",
  "content": "# BM25 Hybrid Search — Design Approved (2026-03-27)\n\n## Decision\nApproved composable retrieval pipeline with BM25 hybrid search after 3 rounds of 5-persona review (Senior SWE, PM, QA, Performance Engineer, API Design Reviewer). All Critical and Important issues resolved. Final round: 5/5 approve, 0 blocking issues.\n\n## Architecture\n4-stage composable pipeline: Searcher → Fusion → Expander → Reranker\n- Generic ComponentRegistry<T> with factory pattern for plug-and-play components\n- NormalizedScore newtype enforces [0,1] fusion contract at type level\n- Per-searcher normalization (each Searcher normalizes own output)\n- ArcSwap hot-swap for runtime A/B benchmarking\n- Arc<KnowledgeEntry> through pipeline to avoid cloning\n- tokio::spawn per searcher for panic isolation + timeout\n\n## BM25 Integration\n- LiteStore: tantivy 0.22 (pure Rust, code-aware tokenizer)\n- PostgresStore: tsvector + ts_rank_cd (native PostgreSQL FTS)\n- FullTextSearchable trait (separate from QueryableStore)\n- Batched commits (100 entries or 500ms), write-generation staleness counter\n\n## Ship Gates\n- Source Recall@5 > 50% (baseline: 37.5%)\n- MRR > 0.60 (baseline: 0.544)\n- No category regression\n- p95 latency < 20ms\n\n## Implementation Phases\nPhase 1: Pipeline abstraction (zero behavioral change)\nPhase 2a/2b/2c: Tantivy + PostgresStore + BM25Searcher+RRF (parallel)\nPhase 3: Integration + hot-swap\nPhase 4: Evaluation + default flip\n\n## Design Doc\nrepos/corvia/docs/rfcs/2026-03-27-hybrid-search-brainstorm.md",
  "source_version": "mcp",
